This vignette demonstrates how the data set `grundy2007` was generated.

```{r}
#| include = FALSE
knitr::opts_chunk$set(
  collapse = TRUE,
  fig.path = "fig-vignettes-example-data-gen-",
  fig.cap = "",
  fig.width = 8.5 / 1.5,
  fig.height = 11 / 2.5,
  fig.retina = 2,
  dpi = 300,
  comment = "#>",
  dev = "ragg_png"
)
```

```{r}
set.seed(42)
n <- 133
correlations <- matrix(
  data = c(
    1, 0.88, 0.84, 0.82, -0.23, -0.12, -0.18, -0.24, -0.38, -0.4, -0.3, -0.37, -0.06, -0.2, -0.22, -0.21, 0.03, -0.04, -0.15, -0.13,
